Responsibilities:
Support business development manager to develop business solutions for Regulator Technologies Asia Pacific.
Perform analysis on customer current architecture, identifying pain and solution opportunity in selected industry.
Work closely with sales, marketing and engineering team to develop solution and customer value messaging.
Build the tools required to effectively drive demand for these solutions such as application brief, pain chain, P&ID, training presentations, Quantified Business Result (QBR) etc.
Train all internal and external sales teams as well as Emerson Process Management teams to build situational fluency.
Drive customer value messaging in integrated marketing events â€“ Tradeshows, Exhibitions and Seminars.
Contribute to Marcom activities and Newsletters with product and solution related updates.
Requirements:
Degree in Mechanical, Electrical, Chemical Engineering or related discipline; Advanced Degree in Marketing or Business preferred.
Minimum of 5 years technical or marketing experience in process industry.
Good human relations and communication skills.
Results-oriented with strong leadership, organizational, planning and problem-solving skills.